<p dir="ltr">With 1 billion tokens up for grabs, players and investors can snap up 75% of the company, with Cryptonia keeping 20% back to fund promotions and tournaments, with only 5% of the total paid out to promoters and advisers to get the room up and running.</p>

<div>
<p dir="ltr">Of course, one of the biggest selling points of crypto-poker rooms over their rivals is the security aspect ‚Äì and the blockchain technology which Cryptonia‚Äôs platform is based on ensures fair play and also helps to avoid delays in payment processing, offering absolute transparency and ease of play.</p>

